  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Child Friendly Spaces and Psycho-Social Activities for Young Syrian Refugees in Jordan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The playgrounds will be set up at existing CFS sites that are over capacity. Although Al-Azraq camp only opened in early May, our CFS&#x2019; receive, on average, over 100-150 children per day. The fenced in sites have large outdoor areas on which to put playgrounds. The playgrounds will be placed on silica sand and surrounded by tires to create an outdoor play area.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project&#x2019;s goal is to respond to the needs of Syrians with an emphasis on children through provision of social and psycho-social support and safe spaces. Mercy Corps will expand upon 4 Child-friendly spaces (CFS) sites and set up playgrounds at each site. Mercy Corps will provide psychosocial and recreational activities for children through sports activities and our Comfort for Kids program. These activities are designed to provide psycho-social support to children who experience extreme stress due to conflict or disaster.

Mercy Corps will also distill lessons learned from over a year of work in Za&#x2019;atari refugee camp, and build upon best practices to ensure enhanced child protection interventions in Al-Azraq camp. Support from the Vibrant Village Foundation will efficiently expand existing child protection programs and ensure that Syrian refugee children have access to services.</narrative>
  </description>
